This shows where or how the invocation to query for Time-Bounded Datapoints may have failed - - Follow the steps below to show more data on queued files 1. Right-click the queue --->a. A pop-up box covering most of the screen will appear once instructions -----> in step 2 have been followed 2. Select 'List Files' 3. Look for an Information icon on the left side of the pop-up box 4. Click the Information icon on the left side of the pop-up box --->a. Another pop-up box will appear 5. This box may have tabs that contain more information when clicked
Token is placed in ORIGINAL flowfile, not response
The BODY of the response flowfile contains the datapoints
The body of the flowfile is updated to contain the required text needed to get time-bounded datapoints
This processor is the end of the flow
TokenResponse is updated to contain only the token instead of the entire response
- - - - - - - - - Predix Time Series is sent a request to get aggregation of datapoints
